text.section:
This subtitle does not apply to:
life insurance;
health insurance;
annuities;
reinsurance;
wet marine and transportation insurance, except as provided in subsection (b) of this section;
insurance on a subject that is located, resident, or to be performed wholly outside the State;
insurance on vehicles or aircraft owned and principally garaged outside the State;
insurance on property or operation of railroads engaged in interstate commerce;
insurance:
on aircraft owned or operated by aircraft manufacturers or operated in scheduled interstate flight;
on cargo of the aircraft described in subitem (i) of this item; or
against liability arising out of the ownership, maintenance, or use of the aircraft described in subitem (i) of this item, other than workers' compensation or employer's liability; or
medical stop-loss insurance, as defined in § 15-129 of this article.
